
[1]invite

   INVI'TE, v.t. [L. invito.]

   1. To ask to do some act or to go to some place; to request the company
   of a person; as, to invite one to dine or sup; to invite friends to a
   wedding; to invite company to an entertainment; to invite one to an
   excursion into the country.

   2. To allure; to draw to; to tempt to come; to induce by pleasure or
   hope.

   --Shady groves, that easy sleep invite.

   3. To present should be in a situation not to invite hostilities.
